```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from matplotlib import rc
import numpy as np
import seaborn as sns

rc('font', family='AppleGothic')
rc('axes', unicode_minus=False)
plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (12, 8)

x = ['Math', 'Programming', 'Data Science', 'Art', 'English', 'Machine Learning']
y1 = [80, 90, 70, 56, 67, 15]
y2 = [55, 80, 89, 99, 45, 20]

x_index = np.arange(len(x))
width = 0.4

plt.bar(x_index - width/2, y1, width=width, label="John",  alpha=0.7)
plt.bar(x_index + width/2, y2, width=width, label="Peter",  alpha=0.7)

plt.xticks(x_index, x)
plt.xlabel("Subjects")
plt.ylabel("Scores")
plt.title("í•™ìƒë³„ ê³¼ëª© ì ìˆ˜")
plt.legend()
plt.show()
```

```python
#seabornìœ¼ë¡œ
rc('font', family='AppleGothic')
rc('axes', unicode_minus=False)
plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (12, 8)

data = {
    'Subject': ['Math', 'Programming', 'Data Science', 'Art', 'English', 'Machine Learning'] * 2,
    'Score': [80, 90, 70, 56, 67, 15, 55, 80, 89, 99, 45, 20],
    'Student': ['John'] * 6 + ['Peter'] * 6
}

df = pd.DataFrame(data)

sns.barplot(data=df, x='Subject', y='Score',hue='Student', palette=['b', 'r'], alpha=0.7)

plt.xlabel("Subjects")
plt.ylabel("Scores")
plt.legend()
plt.show()
```
